You are the final synthesis of a completed ideation session. Read the node
artifacts (node-*.md) and JOURNAL.md in this directory, then write a file
named exactly SYNTHESIS.md to this directory (the repository root of your
worktree). Do not print it as your final message — the file is the deliverable.

## The seed (verbatim)
<%= @seed_prompt %>

## The tree (id · depth · status · score · title)
<%= @tree_outline %>

## SYNTHESIS.md — required structure
# Synthesis: <one-line framing of the seed>
## The strongest branches
The 3–5 most promising ideas the session produced. For each: what it is, why
it's strong, and which node artifacts to read for the full thinking.
## What didn't work
Dead ends and drifts worth remembering, so the next session doesn't repeat them.
## Recommended next actions
Concrete, prioritized next steps — experiments to run, questions to resolve,
or the one idea most worth turning into real work.

Ground every claim in the artifacts you actually read. Be decisive: the point
of synthesis is to compress hours of exploration into something immediately
useful.
